parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering intermediate shaft can cause abnormal noises, vibrations, or clunking sounds while steering, which can lead to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Abnormal noise coming from the steering wheel
clunking or knocking sound while steering

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of the front tires can cause loss of traction, skidding, and accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
The keyless ignition system can cause the engine to remain running in an enclosed space, such as a garage, potentially leading to toxic fume buildup and carbon monoxide poisoning.
symptoms: Engine remains running after leaving the vehicle
failure to automatically turn off the engine after a certain period of inactivity.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The parasitic battery drain can cause the battery to drain excessively, leading to difficulty or failure to start the engine, which can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: even when the vehicle is not in use
difficulty or failure to start the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate violently while braking, leading to brake fading and reduced stopping power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate without driver input, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates without applying pressure to the gas pedal
vehicle continues to accelerate despite depressing the brake pedal
